effortless-ntwf:conc-08-type-c-real a effortless-ntwf:Conclusions ;
    effortless-ntwf:conclusionId "conc-08-type-c-real" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "open-question" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "witnessed" ;
    effortless-ntwf:reportTier "supporting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Does the published literature contain real type-C studies (compression without sign flip)?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:evidence "Witnessed in loop-24: hannan-1994 (CABG surgery), titanic-1912, melanoma-altman-1991, and coffee-tverdal-2020 all hydrate as DistortionType=C. AllocationDistortion>0.01, IsSignFlip=FALSE — the correct pooled direction but compressed magnitude. The type-C cell is not a synthetic pathology." ;
    effortless-ntwf:witnessedInLoop "loop-24" ;
    effortless-ntwf:targetLoop "loop-25" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-epidemiology" ;
    effortless-ntwf:researcherId "researcher-greenland" .

effortless-ntwf:conc-09-causal-vs-geometric a effortless-ntwf:Conclusions ;
    effortless-ntwf:conclusionId "conc-09-causal-vs-geometric" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "open-question" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "witnessed" ;
    effortless-ntwf:reportTier "critical" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "AllocationDistortion is a geometric measure; causal interpretation requires external domain knowledge, gated by AdjustmentAppropriate" ;
    effortless-ntwf:evidence "Berkeley has the highest AllocationDistortion (0.1934) but CausalRole=contested (mediator vs confounder), proving that geometric severity and causal confounding are not the same thing. The instrument is deliberately geometric: it classifies distortion type and flags the corrected winner from allocation arithmetic alone. Whether it is safe to act on that correction as a causal claim is answered by AdjustmentAppropriate — which gates on ConditioningRisk and CausalClaimStatus. The two layers are complementary, not competing. The instrument computes the geometry; the researcher supplies the causal account. This is a scope boundary, not a limitation." ;
    effortless-ntwf:witnessedInLoop "loop-30" ;
    effortless-ntwf:targetLoop "loop-23" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" ;
    effortless-ntwf:researcherId "researcher-dong-cai-zhao" ;
    effortless-ntwf:challengesResearcher "researcher-spirtes-glymour-scheines" .

effortless-ntwf:conc-10-instrument-specifiable a effortless-ntwf:Conclusions ;
    effortless-ntwf:conclusionId "conc-10-instrument-specifiable" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "methodology" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "witnessed" ;
    effortless-ntwf:reportTier "transient" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "The full instrument can be specified precisely enough for any researcher to apply it to a new study" ;
    effortless-ntwf:evidence "Witnessed in loop-26: InstrumentSpec table enumerates 5 input fields, 10 derived coordinates, 2 classification rules, and 3 adapter-requirement rows. Machine-verifiable against the full 90+ study corpus." ;
    effortless-ntwf:witnessedInLoop "loop-26" ;
    effortless-ntwf:targetLoop "loop-30" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-historical" ;
    effortless-ntwf:researcherId "researcher-blyth" .

effortless-ntwf:conc-11-reversal-recovery a effortless-ntwf:Conclusions ;
    effortless-ntwf:conclusionId "conc-11-reversal-recovery" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "instrument" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "witnessed" ;
    effortless-ntwf:reportTier "supporting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "The model can produce the allocation-corrected winner directly from existing DAG fields — no new data required" ;
    effortless-ntwf:evidence "CorrectedGap = WeightedStratumGapSum (already derived in loop-12/17). CorrectedWinner is a sign-read on CorrectedGap. CorrectedVsPooledAgreement is TRUE for Type-D studies and FALSE for Type-A/B studies. For kidney-1986: CorrectedGap=+0.0537, CorrectedWinner=A, CorrectedVsPooledAgreement=FALSE (pooled said B; corrected says A). The reversal recovery is free — it costs zero new data." ;
    effortless-ntwf:witnessedInLoop "loop-27" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" ;
    effortless-ntwf:researcherId "researcher-spirtes-glymour-scheines" .

effortless-ntwf:conc-12-signal-purity-theorem a effortless-ntwf:Conclusions ;
    effortless-ntwf:conclusionId "conc-12-signal-purity-theorem" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "corpus-theorem" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "witnessed" ;
    effortless-ntwf:reportTier "critical" ;
    effortless-ntwf:validatingHypothesis "H-purity" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "SignalPurity < 0.5 is a necessary condition for allocation-driven reversal" ;
    effortless-ntwf:evidence "Witnessed across all reversal studies (type A + B) in the 90+ study corpus: every study with AllocationDirection='reversal' has SignalPurity < 0.5. The algebraic proof: reversal requires SignedPooledGap and CorrectedGap to have opposite signs, which requires AllocationDistortion > |CorrectedGap|, which is exactly SignalPurity < 0.5. inv-signal-purity-sign-flip enforces this as a DAG invariant. AvgSignalPurityReversal ≈ 0.35 vs AvgSignalPurityNonReversal ≈ 0.65 — gap of ~0.30." ;
    effortless-ntwf:witnessedInLoop "loop-44" ;
    effortless-ntwf:targetLoop "loop-44" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

effortless-ntwf:conc-13-cplus-cminus-opposite-errors a effortless-ntwf:Conclusions ;
    effortless-ntwf:conclusionId "conc-13-cplus-cminus-opposite-errors" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "taxonomy" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "witnessed" ;
    effortless-ntwf:reportTier "critical" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "C+ (amplification) and C- (compression) are epistemically opposite errors with opposite clinical implications" ;
    effortless-ntwf:evidence "titanic-1912 (C+, DistortionRatio=1.359): allocation inflates first-class survival advantage from 27.5pp corrected to 37.4pp pooled — overconfidence. melanoma-altman-1991 (C+, DistortionRatio=2.087): allocation doubles apparent female survival advantage — severe overconfidence. hannan-1994 (C-, DistortionRatio=0.314): allocation compresses CABG advantage from 8.9pp corrected to 2.8pp pooled — underconfidence, risk of premature treatment abandonment. The prior type-C category hid this distinction. Now separated by DistortionRatio > 1 (C+) vs DistortionRatio ∈ (0,1) (C-)." ;
    effortless-ntwf:witnessedInLoop "loop-43" ;
    effortless-ntwf:targetLoop "loop-43" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-epidemiology" .

effortless-ntwf:conc-14-scale-is-discovery-path a effortless-ntwf:Conclusions ;
    effortless-ntwf:conclusionId "conc-14-scale-is-discovery-path" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "methodology" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "witnessed" ;
    effortless-ntwf:reportTier "transient" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Cross-domain SignalPurity correlations require a pre-registered unbiased corpus of 50+ studies to distinguish pattern from selection artifact" ;
    effortless-ntwf:evidence "Partial domain patterns witnessed across 90+ studies (loop-61): epidemiology avg distortion 0.050 vs education 0.004; legal/sports/epidemiology flip rates ~27% vs economics 0%. Full causal domain→DistortionType mapping still requires pre-registered expansion beyond convenience sample, but the instrument now supports DiscoveryHypotheses/Findings for ongoing corpus-scale tests." ;
    effortless-ntwf:witnessedInLoop "loop-61" ;
    effortless-ntwf:targetLoop "" .

effortless-ntwf:conc-15-latent-flip-potential a effortless-ntwf:Conclusions ;
    effortless-ntwf:conclusionId "conc-15-latent-flip-potential" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "instrument" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "witnessed" ;
    effortless-ntwf:reportTier "supporting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Type-D at observed allocation does not imply allocation-stable — 70% of SAFE studies flip under counterfactual reweighting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:evidence "LatentTypeDCount=45, TypeDCount=64, LatentTypeDFraction=0.703. LatentFlipPotential=TRUE when DistortionType=D AND PooledGapCrossesZero=TRUE. Examples: uc-systemwide-admissions (Type D, sweep range 0.56), recsys-offline-eval (Type D, sweep range 0.56). The ScreeningTier SAFE label describes observed allocation only; sweep reveals latent flip potential." ;
    effortless-ntwf:witnessedInLoop "loop-61" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-historical" .

effortless-ntwf:conc-16-small-effect-fragile a effortless-ntwf:Conclusions ;
    effortless-ntwf:conclusionId "conc-16-small-effect-fragile" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "instrument" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "witnessed" ;
    effortless-ntwf:reportTier "supporting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "In this corpus, allocation-stable Type-D rows carry larger observed pooled gaps than latent Type-D rows" ;
    effortless-ntwf:evidence "AvgPooledGapStableD=0.102 across 19 stable Type-D studies; AvgPooledGapLatentD=0.022 across 45 latent Type-D studies. Stable studies also have lower sweep range (avg 0.072 vs 0.211). Corpus-descriptive pattern on loop-61 convenience sample — not a deductive law. Small observed effects tend to be allocation-fragile even when currently classified SAFE." ;
    effortless-ntwf:witnessedInLoop "loop-61" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

effortless-ntwf:conc-17-economics-flip-free a effortless-ntwf:Conclusions ;
    effortless-ntwf:conclusionId "conc-17-economics-flip-free" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "corpus-pattern-superseded" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "historical" ;
    effortless-ntwf:reportTier "transient" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Economics-domain 2×K encodings in this corpus produce zero sign-flips — composition studies read as Type D or C−" ;
    effortless-ntwf:evidence "EconomicsSignFlipCount=0 across 8 economics studies (6 Type D, 2 Type C−). Contrast epidemiology (6 sign-flips / 22 studies, 27.3%). Composition and wage-decomposition paradoxes compress or stabilize rather than flip in this instrument's 2×K encoding. **Superseded at loop-78 (N=238):** EconomicsSignFlipCount=10 (25.6% flip rate) after expansion wave 3 bulk encode — pattern was corpus-contingent on pre-expansion selection, not a domain law." ;
    effortless-ntwf:witnessedInLoop "loop-61" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-epidemiology" .

effortless-ntwf:conc-18-causal-role-flip-mode a effortless-ntwf:Conclusions ;
    effortless-ntwf:conclusionId "conc-18-causal-role-flip-mode" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "instrument" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "witnessed" ;
    effortless-ntwf:reportTier "supporting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Causal role predicts manifest vs latent reversal mode — confounders flip at observed allocation; collider/selection flips stay sweep-latent" ;
    effortless-ntwf:evidence "Loop-62 research sweep: H-causal-manifest PASS (confFlip=15 vs collManifest=0). H-causal-latent PASS (collManifest=0, collLatent=5, collN=7). Confounder Type-D rows often show latent-only sweep sensitivity (45 latent-only) without manifest sign-flip — the mechanism split is about reversal mode when sign-flips occur, not absence of sweep fragility. Existing LatentFlipPotential + StratumCausalRole suffice; defer ManifestReversal first-class fields to loop-67+." ;
    effortless-ntwf:witnessedInLoop "loop-62" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

effortless-ntwf:conc-19-explained-tracks-confounding a effortless-ntwf:Conclusions ;
    effortless-ntwf:conclusionId "conc-19-explained-tracks-confounding" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "instrument" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "witnessed" ;
    effortless-ntwf:reportTier "supporting" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "IsParadoxExplained tracks adjust-resolvable confounding, not geometric distortion" ;
    effortless-ntwf:evidence "In this corpus, IsParadoxExplained=TRUE iff the study has a manifest sign-flip driven by a confounder — i.e. stratification resolves the reversal. It is FALSE for all C+/C−/D types, and FALSE for the three contested/mediator sign-flips (berkeley-1973, berkeley-six-dept-1973, birth-weight-paradox). The boundary separates 'stratify immediately' from 'do not naively adjust for a collider or mediator'." ;
    effortless-ntwf:witnessedInLoop "loop-63" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

effortless-ntwf:conc-20-signal-purity-ceiling a effortless-ntwf:Conclusions ;
    effortless-ntwf:conclusionId "conc-20-signal-purity-ceiling" ;
    effortless-ntwf:category "corpus-theorem" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "witnessed" ;
    effortless-ntwf:reportTier "critical" ;
    effortless-ntwf:validatingHypothesis "H-purity" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "SignalPurity < 0.5 is a build-breaking invariant for sign-flip studies — witnessed at corpus scale" ;
    effortless-ntwf:evidence "At 96-study corpus scale, every manifest sign-flip has SignalPurity strictly below 0.5 (corpus max: 0.483, jeter-justice-1997). The melanoma-altman-1991 boundary case (purity=0.479, C+, pooled gap crosses zero, no flip) confirms the law is tight but not violated. This graduates from corpus hypothesis (loop-61) to build-breaking invariant: any future study encoding that produces a sign-flip with purity >= 0.5 is an encoding error, not a counterexample." ;
    effortless-ntwf:witnessedInLoop "loop-64" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

