effortless-ntwf:loop-26 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-26" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Instrument specification: adapter contract, five input fields, four output types" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "InstrumentSpec table: one row per required input field, derived coordinate, classification rule, and adapter contract requirement. Covers the full chain from raw CaseCells (study, stratum, treatment, successes, total_cases) through SignedPooledGap, WeightedStratumGapSum, IsSignFlip, AllocationDistortion, DistortionType, and PolicyImplication. Every row machine-verifiable against the hydrated studies." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "Can the full instrument be stated precisely enough that another researcher or script can hydrate a new study and classify it without access to the internal DAG? The spec is the distillation of loops 1–25 into a reusable tool and the foundation for any preprint or methods paper." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "The instrument specification is the terminal deliverable. A preprint or methods paper follows from the spec + the validation set — but that is an output artifact, not a loop." ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-historical" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitHash "ca3109557acb34bb159bed0ac1c39e5a81cce5dc" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitDate "2026-06-27" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitMessage "loop-20+20b: real study hydration via 05b-customize-data.sql — two type-A reversals witnessed" ;
    effortless-ntwf:gitTag "sp-loop-milestone-04-loops-16-31" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-27 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-27" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Reversal Recovery: the corrected treatment signal as a first-class derived fact" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "CorrectedGap (= WeightedStratumGapSum, named with intent), CorrectedWinner, CorrectedVsPooledAgreement on TreatmentRankings. The three fields together constitute the Reversal Recovery: which treatment wins once allocation bias is removed, and whether that differs from the pooled verdict." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "Given the observed allocation distortion, which treatment would a researcher conclude is better if the allocation artifact were corrected? Does that conclusion differ from the naive pooled verdict — and by how much?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "Loop 28 could introduce a CorrectedPolicyImplication field that derives the appropriate research action from CorrectedWinner + DistortionType together, superseding the allocation-unaware PolicyImplication for Types A and B studies." ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitHash "ca3109557acb34bb159bed0ac1c39e5a81cce5dc" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitDate "2026-06-27" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitMessage "loop-20+20b: real study hydration via 05b-customize-data.sql — two type-A reversals witnessed" ;
    effortless-ntwf:gitTag "sp-loop-milestone-04-loops-16-31" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-28 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-28" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "CorrectedPolicyImplication: allocation-aware action replaces the naive verdict for Types A and B" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "CorrectedPolicyImplication on TreatmentRankings: derives the researcher action from CorrectedWinner + DistortionType together. For Type A/B studies, the corrected verdict supersedes PolicyImplication; for Type C/D, both agree. Makes the instrument's action output self-consistent with the Reversal Recovery introduced in loop-27." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "When the corrected winner differs from the pooled winner, what should a researcher do — and does the instrument tell them clearly, or does it give two contradictory action fields?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "Loop 29 must audit every derived formula for internal consistency: balanced allocation ⇒ AllocationDistortion=0; Type D ⇒ CorrectedVsPooledAgreement=TRUE; Type A ⇒ CorrectedVsPooledAgreement=FALSE. These are not empirical claims — they are algebraic invariants. Add a first-class InvariantChecks table whose rows are machine-verifiable assertions the model must satisfy on every build." ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-ai-fairness" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitHash "ca3109557acb34bb159bed0ac1c39e5a81cce5dc" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitDate "2026-06-27" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitMessage "loop-20+20b: real study hydration via 05b-customize-data.sql — two type-A reversals witnessed" ;
    effortless-ntwf:gitTag "sp-loop-milestone-04-loops-16-31" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-29 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-29" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "InvariantChecks: algebraic self-consistency as first-class witnessed assertions" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "InvariantChecks table: one row per algebraic invariant (balanced allocation → AllocationDistortion=0; Type D → CorrectedVsPooledAgreement=TRUE; IsSignFlip → CorrectedWinner≠PooledWinner; WeightedStratumGapSum = Σ(StratumFraction×StratumGap); etc.). Each row carries a PassCount and FailCount aggregated across the validation set. Any FailCount>0 is a build-breaking bug, not a data anomaly." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "Is the model algebraically self-consistent across the full 90+ study corpus? Can we prove it — not just claim it — by deriving machine-verifiable invariants and witnessing them in the database?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "Loop 33 must lock the hydration and provenance story to a single canonical account. Real data enters via one path (rulebook JSON as SSoT; 05b-customize-data.sql is a build artifact). Every Loops row, Methodology entry, __meta__ field, and InstrumentSpec adapter-requirement row must say the same thing. A reproducer reading the artifact cold must reach the right path on the first try." ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitHash "ca3109557acb34bb159bed0ac1c39e5a81cce5dc" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitDate "2026-06-27" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitMessage "loop-20+20b: real study hydration via 05b-customize-data.sql — two type-A reversals witnessed" ;
    effortless-ntwf:gitTag "sp-loop-milestone-04-loops-16-31" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-30 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-30" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Causality Boundary Layer: separate geometric distortion from causal interpretation" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "CausalClaimStatus (established | contested | geometric-only) and AdjustmentAppropriate (boolean with rationale) on TreatmentRankings. ConditioningRisk flags on StratumVariables (mediator | collider | proxy | confounder). Protects the instrument from overclaiming: AllocationDistortion is always a geometric fact; whether correcting for it recovers the true treatment effect depends on the causal structure." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "When is CorrectedGap the right estimate to report, and when is it still wrong? Does adjusting for a mediator or collider make things worse? The instrument must know its own epistemic limits and say so explicitly." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "After loop-33 the instrument is publishable as a methods paper: allocation-aware action guidance (loop-28), algebraic self-consistency (loop-29), clean provenance (loop-30), structural integrity + honest weighting (loop-31), cherry-picking defense (loop-32), and causality honesty (loop-33). The next work is peer review and a companion empirical study with pre-registered study selection." ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitHash "ca3109557acb34bb159bed0ac1c39e5a81cce5dc" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitDate "2026-06-27" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitMessage "loop-20+20b: real study hydration via 05b-customize-data.sql — two type-A reversals witnessed" ;
    effortless-ntwf:gitTag "sp-loop-milestone-04-loops-16-31" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-31 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-31" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Provenance Contract: one canonical source-of-truth story, zero contradictory docstrings" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "ProvenanceAudit: a sweep of every Loops row, Methodology entry, __meta__ field, InstrumentSpec adapter-requirement, and 05b header comment for contradictions about where real data lives and how a reproducer seeds a new study. All resolved to a single canonical account. No loop row may claim a different hydration path than another." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "If a researcher reads only the artifact — no prior context, no conversation — do they arrive at the correct seeding procedure? Or do some docstrings point to SQL, some to JSON, and some to neither?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "Loop 33 must complete structural integrity: every study has exactly 2 treatment rows, every stratum has exactly one A-cell and one B-cell, every TreatmentRanking FK resolves to a valid Study. Missing rows flagged and added; orphaned rows identified and removed. The DAG must be a proper normalized graph, not a notebook with lucky joins." ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitHash "ca3109557acb34bb159bed0ac1c39e5a81cce5dc" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitDate "2026-06-27" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitMessage "loop-20+20b: real study hydration via 05b-customize-data.sql — two type-A reversals witnessed" ;
    effortless-ntwf:gitTag "sp-loop-milestone-04-loops-16-31" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-32 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-32" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Structural Integrity + Sample-Size Weighting: a proper normalized DAG and epistemically honest ModelSummary" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "RelationshipIntegrityValidator: assertions that every study has ≥2 strata, exactly 2 treatment labels, paired A/B cells per stratum, and every FK resolves. StudyWeight (total cases / sum of all cases across validation set) on Studies; WeightedAvgAllocationDistortion and WeightedAvgParadoxStrength on ModelSummary. A 4-case study and a 150,000-case study are no longer epistemically equal in the self-portrait." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "Is the model a proper normalized DAG with no missing links? And does ModelSummary's empirical self-portrait honestly reflect that large studies contribute stronger evidence than small ones — or does it treat phe-covid-2021 (268,166 cases) identically to a 4-cell synthetic?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "Loop 33 must define the validation protocol — inclusion/exclusion criteria and minimum cell counts — so the empirical generalization claim is not vulnerable to a cherry-picking objection. Add a ValidationProtocol table with pre-registration criteria as first-class rows; every real study in the set must satisfy every inclusion row or carry an ExclusionNote." ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-epidemiology" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitHash "a6e0725cbcbeb17a49c11dbcad061f770de2293e" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitDate "2026-06-27" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitMessage "feat: enhance README and server to support standalone explorer; add new screenshots" ;
    effortless-ntwf:gitTag "sp-loop-milestone-05-loops-23b-33" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-33 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-33" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Validation Protocol: inclusion/exclusion criteria and cherry-picking defense" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "ValidationProtocol table: one row per inclusion/exclusion criterion (minimum cell count ≥ 10 per cell; binary treatment; outcome direction pre-registered; stratum variable named before classification; no post-hoc stratum splitting). Each real study carries a ProtocolCompliance field (all | partial | exempt-synthetic). Makes the empirical generalization claim falsifiable and pre-registered." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "Could a reviewer accuse the validation set of being hand-picked to make the instrument look good? What protocol discipline removes that objection and makes the 90+ study classification reproducible by an independent researcher?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "Loop 30 must add the causality boundary layer — explicitly separate what the geometry says (AllocationDistortion, CorrectedGap) from what the causal interpretation claims (IsConfounder, CausalRole). Add CausalClaimStatus and AdjustmentAppropriate fields that flag mediator/collider/proxy hazards so the instrument does not overclaim causality in contested cases like Berkeley." ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitHash "a6e0725cbcbeb17a49c11dbcad061f770de2293e" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitDate "2026-06-27" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitMessage "feat: enhance README and server to support standalone explorer; add new screenshots" ;
    effortless-ntwf:gitTag "sp-loop-milestone-05-loops-23b-33" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-34 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-34" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "AllocationInvariance: CorrectedGap is the conserved quantity — empirically witnessed" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "AllocationSweep table: a parametric sweep of treatment-A allocation fraction within kidney-1986's large stratum (10 rows, f_L from 0.05 to 0.95). Stratum totals and per-stratum rates are fixed; only the A/B split varies. Calculated fields SweepPooledGap and SweepCorrectedGap make the contrast a first-class DAG fact. Two new InvariantChecks: (1) SweepCorrectedGapRange < 0.0001 (the corrected gap is allocation-free); (2) SweepPooledGapRange > 0.10 (the pooled gap genuinely wanders). Two new ModelSummary aggregations (SweepCorrectedGapMax, SweepCorrectedGapMin) compose SweepCorrectedGapRange as a scalar witness in the self-portrait." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "Is CorrectedGap (= WeightedStratumGapSum) genuinely invariant under re-stratification — or does it move when the allocation shifts? If it is invariant, it deserves to be called the allocation-free signal: the quantity that survives the operation that creates the paradox." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "loop-35: extend AllocationSweep to all four distortion types and add SweepStudySummary one-row-per-study aggregation + UI sweep slider" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-historical" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitHash "5a14dcb9e84aaf645e19965933246fdc0cb76e34" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitDate "2026-06-28" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitMessage "Add new metrics and definitions for allocation sweep analysis" ;
    effortless-ntwf:gitTag "sp-loop-milestone-06-loops-34-57" .

