effortless-ntwf:loop-43 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-43" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "C+/C-: allocation amplification vs compression as distinct epistemic errors" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "DistortionType values C+ (DistortionRatio>1, amplification) and C- (DistortionRatio in (0,1), compression); AllocationDirection field (reversal/amplification/compression/neutral); CAmplificationCount and CCompressionCount on ModelSummary; InvariantChecks inv-cplus-ratio-gt-1 and inv-cminus-ratio-in-01." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "The existing type-C category collapses two epistemically opposite errors: C+ (allocation inflates effect, causing researcher overconfidence) and C- (allocation suppresses effect, causing researcher underconfidence and possible premature treatment abandonment). Can the instrument separate these with distinct labels, invariants, and policy implications?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:mockDataNote "Witnessed from DB: hannan-1994 → C- (DistortionRatio=0.314 — true CABG advantage 8.9pp, pooled shows 2.8pp; underconfidence). titanic-1912 → C+ (DistortionRatio=1.359 — true first-class survival advantage 27.5pp, pooled shows 37.4pp; overconfidence). melanoma-altman-1991 → C+ (DistortionRatio=2.087 — true female survival advantage 8.6pp, pooled shows 18pp). InvariantChecks pass. C+ and C- are mechanically distinguishable by whether DistortionRatio > 1 or DistortionRatio < 1." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "loop-44: Add SignalPurity = |CorrectedGap| / (|CorrectedGap| + AllocationDistortion). Witness the theorem: AllocationDirection='reversal' → SignalPurity < 0.5. This is the mechanistic account of why reversals happen." ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-historical" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitHash "5a14dcb9e84aaf645e19965933246fdc0cb76e34" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitDate "2026-06-28" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitMessage "Add new metrics and definitions for allocation sweep analysis" ;
    effortless-ntwf:gitTag "sp-loop-milestone-06-loops-34-57" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-44 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-44" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "SignalPurity theorem: reversal requires noise > signal — witnessed as a DAG invariant" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "SignalPurity field on TreatmentRankings (|CorrectedGap| / (|CorrectedGap| + AllocationDistortion)); inv-signal-purity-sign-flip InvariantCheck; AvgSignalPurity on ModelSummary." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "Is there a single threshold separating studies where the pooled conclusion is directionally trustworthy from studies where it is not? The theorem: when SignalPurity < 0.5 (allocation noise exceeds true signal), the pooled direction cannot be trusted. Does the instrument witness this across all real reversal studies?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:mockDataNote "Witnessed from DB: all type-A/B studies (AllocationDirection=reversal) have SignalPurity < 0.5 — the confound is doing more than half the work. All type-C and D studies have SignalPurity >= 0.5 except melanoma-altman-1991 (C+, ~0.479) — the known exception where amplification pushes AllocationDistortion > |CorrectedGap| without a sign flip because amplification adds to rather than subtracts from the signal. inv-signal-purity-sign-flip passes across all reversal studies. AvgSignalPurity across real studies ≈ 0.38 — the average real study in this validation set is allocation-noise-dominated. This is the first quantitative claim in this instrument that could not be derived from the standard Simpson's Paradox literature: the confound is generating more apparent signal than the treatment itself across the corpus." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "The five-cell taxonomy (A, B, C+, C-, D) with SignalPurity as a continuous severity axis is now complete. Next question: does SignalPurity correlate with domain, sample size, or causal role? Add ByDomain breakdown to test whether the confound mechanism is domain-specific." ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitHash "5a14dcb9e84aaf645e19965933246fdc0cb76e34" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitDate "2026-06-28" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitMessage "Add new metrics and definitions for allocation sweep analysis" ;
    effortless-ntwf:gitTag "sp-loop-milestone-06-loops-34-57" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-45 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-45" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "ModelSummary TypeC subtype counts: TypeCPlusCount and TypeCMinusCount" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "TypeCPlusCount, TypeCMinusCount" ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "How many studies are C+ vs C- — i.e. how many have allocation that amplifies vs attenuates the pooled signal without reversing it?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:mockDataNote "Witnessed from DB: CAmplificationCount=2 (titanic-1912 C+ DistortionRatio=1.359, melanoma-altman-1991 C+ DistortionRatio=2.087), CCompressionCount=2 (hannan-1994 C- DistortionRatio=0.314, plus one synthetic). TypeCPlusCount and TypeCMinusCount verified in vw_model_summary. ModelSummary DistortionTaxonomyCoverage now reads: A:5 B:4 C+:2 C-:2 D:3. DistortionOnlyCount=4 (C+ + C-)." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "loop-46: Rulespeak regen — update human-readable narrative with five-type taxonomy and InstrumentScore" ;
