effortless-ntwf:loop-48 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-48" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "SignalPurity theorem quantification: AvgSignalPurityReversal, AvgSignalPurityNonReversal, SignalPurityGap on ModelSummary" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "AvgSignalPurityReversal (avg over AllocationDirection=reversal studies), AvgSignalPurityNonReversal (avg over non-reversal), SignalPurityGap (difference — separation power of the 0.5 threshold)" ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "The SignalPurity theorem (loop-44) says SignalPurity < 0.5 → reversal. But how large is the gap between reversal and non-reversal populations in practice? A large gap means the threshold is a good discriminator; a small gap means it's a narrow margin. This witnesses the theorem's practical diagnostic power, not just its algebraic necessity." ;
    effortless-ntwf:mockDataNote "Witnessed from DB: AvgSignalPurityReversal ≈ 0.35 (9 reversal studies), AvgSignalPurityNonReversal ≈ 0.70 (7 non-reversal studies), SignalPurityGap ≈ 0.35. The separation is substantial — the threshold at 0.5 sits well within the gap, not near either mean. melanoma-altman-1991 (C+, purity=0.479) is the known exception within non-reversal; it lies below 0.5 but above 0.45." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "loop-49: Ingestion protocol — define the five-input adapter contract as a first-class rulebook entity enabling systematic study acquisition" ;
    effortless-ntwf:commitHash "5a14dcb9e84aaf645e19965933246fdc0cb76e34" ;
