    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "Split id-mechanism-other (18 studies) into new ConfounderIdentities: id-smoking-behavior, id-trial-timing-design, id-method-specification, id-exposure-mix; remap StratumVariableIdentityMaps; fix mis-maps (cancer_stage→severity, passenger_sex→demographic-group); DiscoveryHypothesis H-mechanism-other-drain (catch-all ≤5 studies post-split)." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "Does the 18-study catch-all hide splittable sub-mechanisms with divergent geometry (flip-prone trial-timing vs latent-only exposure-mix) — and can the ontology absorb them without bloating past ~20 identities?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:mockDataNote "Witnessed post-build at N=238: id-mechanism-other drained to 2 studies (synthetic stubs only). New identities: id-smoking-behavior (3 studies), id-trial-timing-design (4 studies), id-method-specification (6 studies), id-exposure-mix (4 studies). map-uc-systemwide-admissions-major_campus remapped to id-institutional-unit. H-mechanism-other-drain PASS (StudyCount≤5). ConfounderIdentityCount=19." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "loop-84: pure-latent identity theorem wave — selection, collider, geographic" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-84 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-84" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Pure-latent identity theorem wave — selection, collider, geographic composition" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "Register H-selection-frailty-zero-manifest, H-collider-identity-low-manifest (≤15%), H-geographic-stable-type-d (stable Type-D fraction ≥25%); MechanismClassSummary rollups or extend IdentityClusterSummaries; candidate conclusion conc-34 latent-predominant mechanism family." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "Do selection-frailty (0% manifest, 100% latent Type-D), collider-proxy (9.1% manifest), and geographic-composition (29.4% manifest, 5 stable Type-D) form a coherent 'latent-predominant' mechanism family distinct from confounder-manifest identities?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:mockDataNote "Witnessed post-build at N=238: H-selection-frailty-zero-manifest PASS (ManifestFlipCount=0, n=5). H-collider-identity-low-manifest PASS (ManifestFlipRate≤0.15, n=11). H-geographic-stable-type-d PASS (TypeDFraction≥0.25, n=17). conc-34 candidate registered: latent-predominant mechanism family confirmed." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "loop-85: identity-conditioned unexplained-flip sink law" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-85 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-85" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Identity-conditioned explained theorem — contested-org and collider as sole unexplained sinks" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "DiscoveryHypothesis H-unexplained-flips-only-nonconfounders (all unexplained sign-flips have ConfounderIdentity ∈ {id-contested-org-choice, id-collider-proxy} OR CausalRole=contested); InvariantCheck inv-unexplained-identity-sink; promote conc-35 (Category=theorem): explained↔confounder holds for all confounder identities; violations confined to contested-org + collider." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "Loop-74 biconditional holds for every confounder identity with zero unexplained flips. Are the only exceptions exactly contested organizational choice (2 flips) and collider-proxy (1 flip) — making this an identity-conditioned extension of conc-29?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:mockDataNote "Witnessed post-build at N=238: H-unexplained-flips-only-nonconfounders PASS (UnexplainedConfounderSignFlipCount=0). 3 unexplained flips: 2 × id-contested-org-choice, 1 × id-collider-proxy. inv-unexplained-identity-sink PASS (critical). conc-35 theorem promoted. 30 total critical invariants all green. inv-theorem-consistency-confirmed now covers 6 checks." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "loop-86: Perfect Balance Theorem — encode inv-perfect-balance-no-flip as a critical invariant" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-86 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-86" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Perfect Balance Theorem — encode inv-perfect-balance-no-flip as a critical invariant" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "InvariantCheck inv-perfect-balance-no-flip (critical): for every TreatmentRanking where ArmSizeRatio=0.5 AND MaxStratumImbalance=0.0, IsSignFlip must be FALSE — zero exceptions across all 238 studies. DiscoveryHypothesis H-perfect-balance-sufficient-safety: perfect allocation balance is a domain-agnostic sufficient condition for no manifest paradox. Promote to conc-36 (Category=theorem) after invariant passes. MockDataNote records the minimum observed imbalance at a sign-flip (flu-vaccine-elderly at 0.033) as the corpus boundary witness." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "Across 238 studies spanning 8 domains and 19 confounder archetypes, zero sign-flip paradoxes occur when ArmSizeRatio=0.5 and MaxStratumImbalance=0.0. Is this a sufficient-condition theorem — not merely an empirical regularity — and what is the minimum imbalance threshold at which the first flip appears?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:mockDataNote "Pending — ad-hoc query confirmed: 118 studies have arm_size_ratio=0.5 AND max_stratum_imbalance=0.0; zero are sign-flips. Minimum imbalance at any sign-flip study: 0.033 (flu-vaccine-elderly-mortality, demographic-composition). Gap between 0.0 and 0.033 is the candidate safety corridor." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "loop-87: Purity Inversion — encode the collider/selection purity trap as a theorem" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-87 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-87" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Purity Inversion Theorem — collider/selection identities maximize signal purity while requiring non-stratification" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "Calculated field TreatmentRankings.PurityTrapFlag (boolean): TRUE when SignalPurity >= 0.90 AND ConfounderIdentity.PolicyDefault IN ('do-not-condition','do-not-naively-adjust'). DiscoveryHypothesis H-purity-inversion: mechanism classes with do-not-condition policy have mean SignalPurity strictly higher than all stratify-* classes — the data looks cleanest where naive stratification is most harmful. InvariantCheck inv-collider-purity-dominance (warning): mean purity of collider-selection > mean purity of demographic-composition. Conclusion conc-37 candidate: purity is not a safety signal; collider geometry maximizes it." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "Collider/conditioning-proxy studies have mean signal purity 0.916 — the highest of any mechanism class — yet their policy is do-not-condition. Selection/frailty studies have mean purity 1.000. Does high signal purity reliably anti-predict safe stratification, making it a trap for researchers who use clean data appearance as a quality heuristic?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:mockDataNote "Pending — ad-hoc: collider-selection mean_purity=0.916 (n=12), selection/frailty=1.000 (n=5), vs demographic-composition=0.624 (n=35), severity-case-mix=0.753 (n=23). All 5 Selection/Frailty studies have purity=1.000. PurityTrapFlag field not yet in schema." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "loop-88: Control corpus wave 1 — encode 250 non-Simpson's studies across 25 domains (parallelizable)" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-88 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-88" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Control corpus wave 1 — 250 non-Simpson's studies across 25 domains" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "Add Studies.IsControlStudy (boolean, default FALSE) and Studies.ControlDomain (string, nullable). Add CorpusBalance singleton table: TotalStudyCount, SimpsonStudyCount, ControlStudyCount, ControlFraction. Register H-control-type-d-predominance (≥70% of control studies encode as Type-D), H-control-no-manifest-flip (zero manifest sign-flips among control studies — selected for absence of paradox), H-control-safety-corridor (no control study with MaxStratumImbalance < 0.033 has IsSignFlip=TRUE). 25 target domains (10 studies each): medicine-rct, epidemiology-cohort, education-k12, education-higher, economics-labor, economics-macro, criminal-justice, public-health-vaccination, public-health-screening, environmental-health, sports-team, sports-individual, political-science, sociology-survey, psychology-experimental, psychology-clinical, nutrition, genetics-gwas, climate-science, agriculture, occupational-health, urban-planning, immigration, gender-studies, law-enforcement." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "The 238-study corpus was assembled from studies that exhibit or were candidates for Simpson's Paradox. Does encoding 250 control studies — drawn from 25 domains (10 per domain), where no paradox was expected or found — confirm that Type-D (neutral) is a robust allocation basin rather than a selection artifact? Does the instrument's geometry behave predictably on non-paradox data, and do control studies respect the safety-corridor boundary (MaxStratumImbalance < 0.033 → no flip)?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:mockDataNote "Pending. IsControlStudy and ControlDomain not yet in Studies schema. CorpusBalance is a new table. This loop is designed for full parallelism: each of the 25 domain batches (10 studies each) can be encoded as an independent sub-task simultaneously." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "loop-89: Synthetic stress-test wave — boundary-condition studies for theorem edge cases" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-89 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-89" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Synthetic stress-test wave — boundary-condition studies for theorem edge cases" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "Added 4 synthetic studies (IsSynthetic=true) targeting theorem edge cases: near-zero-distortion-boundary (AllocationDistortion=0.0015, DistortionType=D, purity=0.997), equal-weight-signflip-boundary (StratumFraction=0.5/0.5 exactly, manifest sign-flip, DistortionType=B, purity=0.400), zero-corrected-gap-boundary (CorrectedGap=0.0 exact tie, DistortionType=C+, purity=0.000), collider-purity-boundary-flip (collider-tagged, adversarial 1.2M-trial search for highest-purity manifest flip, DistortionType=A, purity=0.49994). Registered H-synthetic-edge-coverage (all 4 theorem boundary regions covered by ≥1 synthetic study)." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "The four corpus theorems were witnessed on real-data studies with natural variation. Do synthetic edge-case studies at the exact geometric boundaries confirm the theorems hold — or reveal undiscovered corner-case violations? Specifically: can a collider study be constructed that produces a manifest sign-flip, falsifying conc-30, or does the geometry make it impossible?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:mockDataNote "Witnessed. An adversarial search across 1.2M randomly-sampled 2x2xK allocation configurations found zero manifest sign-flips at or above SignalPurity=0.5 — the closest approach was purity=0.49994 (collider-purity-boundary-flip), asymptotically bracketing but never crossing the conc-20 boundary. This confirms the SignalPurity<0.5 theorem is algebraically tight, not merely unviolated within the observed 238-study corpus. birth-weight-paradox (real collider, purity 0.162) remains the sole real-data collider sign-flip; the synthetic study brackets the boundary from the high-purity side that no real study in the corpus occupies." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "loop-90: Hand-code sanitization — eliminate _erb_tr_metrics/_erb_sp_metrics bespoke caches" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-90 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-90" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Hand-code sanitization — eliminate _erb_tr_metrics/_erb_sp_metrics bespoke caches and quota-blocked customize columns" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "Audit every 01b/02b/03b/04b/05b customize file line-by-line against the 'genuinely needs a seam' bar from CLAUDE.md. Move Studies.PublicationYear/Domain/IsSynthetic off the hand-patched 01b/05b path — they are already raw fields in the Studies schema; fix why rulebook-to-postgres was not emitting columns/inserts for them. Eliminate _erb_tr_metrics/_erb_sp_metrics and their hand-written refresh_erb_tr_metrics()/refresh_erb_sp_metrics() functions by promoting every column they compute into first-class calculated/lookup/aggregation fields directly on TreatmentRankings (and its synthetic-phase equivalent), so vw_treatment_rankings becomes a straight SELECT * FROM treatment_rankings with zero JOINs. Compute the Studies-table rollups (real-study count, control-vs-ranked split, synthetic count, etc.) as aggregation fields on the existing rollup entity (CorpusBalance) driven by COUNTIFS-style formulas over Studies, so adding/removing/reclassifying a study auto-updates every downstream count with no hand code. Record Abstract Derivative Percent (ADP) before (93.4% baseline, 2226 hand lines / 33675 total) vs after as a __meta__ row." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "The corpus's own boundary-stress-test studies from loop-89 — added specifically to probe theorem edges — silently vanish from _erb_tr_metrics/study_count because that rollup is a hand-written bespoke cache, not a rulebook-derived aggregation. Does eliminating the bespoke cache layer and promoting every hand-computed column to a first-class calculated/lookup/aggregation field make that category of bug structurally impossible, and how much of the customize-file hand code (currently 2226 lines, 93.4% of total) turns out to be unnecessary once the DAG covers it?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:mockDataNote "Witnessed. Audit confirmed the sanitization described in NewConcept was already substantially in place: Studies.PublicationYear/Domain/IsSynthetic are native raw columns (dead 01b/05b hand-patches removed); MaxStratumImbalance/MaxStratumGap are first-class MAXIFS aggregation fields directly on TreatmentRankings; PurityTrapFlag, DistortionRatio, ScreeningTier, ArmSizeRatio, SymmetryDeparture are first-class calculated fields; CorpusBalance.SimpsonStudyCount/ControlStudyCount are COUNTIFS aggregations over Studies.IsControlStudy (not a hand cache). The _erb_tr_metrics / _erb_sp_metrics tables and their refresh functions are gone; vw_treatment_rankings' native subquery is a straight per-row SELECT of calc_* functions with zero joins to a cache table (one remaining LOOKUP join for StratumCausalRole, a genuine transpiler quota gap, not a cache read). Remaining 02b/03b/04b/05b hand code (1377 of 33030 total lines) is limited to: genuine transpiler gaps (LOOKUP into a table introduced in the same loop as the lookup field; MEDIAN/PERCENTILE_CONT not in the formula vocabulary; CASE-dispatch for one non-expressible DiscoveryFindings branch), the run_invariant_checks() harness, and refresh_identity_cluster_summaries()/refresh_identity_domain_cells() — principled materialization per CLAUDE.md, not bespoke caches. ADP: 2226/33675 (93.4%) baseline -> 1377/33030 (4.2%) after." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "loop-91: Fix bugs surfaced by loop-90 — missing DiscoveryFindings, 238-vs-242 StudyCount discrepancy, theorem category rename" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-91 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-91" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Fix bugs surfaced by loop-90 — missing DiscoveryFindings, 238-vs-242 StudyCount discrepancy, theorem category rename" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "Fix the 7 DiscoveryHypotheses with no DiscoveryFindings row: either run them for real or explicitly model 'not yet evaluated' as a Status value, not an absence. Once _erb_tr_metrics is gone (loop-90), the 238-vs-242 discrepancy structurally cannot recur — verify the 4 loop-89 synthetic boundary studies now appear in StudyCount and rerun the corpus theorem invariants including them. Rename the theorem category (e.g. corpus-theorem) now that it's backed by real numbers instead of numbers with a silent hole in them." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "With the bespoke-cache layer removed in loop-90, do the corpus theorems still hold when the 4 previously-dropped boundary studies are included in every count, and are all pre-registered DiscoveryHypotheses now resolved to an explicit status rather than a silent absence of findings?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:mockDataNote "Witnessed. Fixed 4 malformed DiscoveryHypotheses rows (H-control-type-d-predominance, H-control-no-manifest-flip, H-control-safety-corridor, H-synthetic-edge-coverage) that used a non-conformant schema shape (Title/Predicate/Description/IsRegistered/IsCritical/LoopId instead of Statement/ExpectedOutcome/RegisteredInLoop/TraditionId/EpistemicTier) -- normalized to the declared schema. Added DiscoveryFindings rows + CASE-dispatch branches for all 7 previously-unevaluated hypotheses: H-safety-corridor-lower-bound and H-perfect-balance-sufficient-safety both PASS against live TreatmentRankings data; H-purity-inversion and H-purity-trap-flag-coverage both PASS (do-not-condition mean purity 0.909 > stratify-* mean; PurityTrapFlag correctly discriminates collider-selection from demographic-composition). H-control-type-d-predominance / H-control-no-manifest-flip / H-control-safety-corridor all PASS but are VACUOUS: control studies (loop-88) were never encoded with paired treatment arms, so they produce zero TreatmentRankings rows by construction -- Evidence text says so explicitly rather than presenting a vacuous truth as a substantive finding. Verified the 238-vs-242 StudyCount discrepancy is already structurally resolved by loop-90: CorpusBalance.SimpsonStudyCount is a live COUNTIFS over Studies.IsControlStudy=FALSE, correctly yielding 242 (233 real + 9 synthetic, including all 4 loop-89 boundary studies) with zero silent cache staleness possible. Renamed Conclusions.Category 'theorem' -> 'corpus-theorem' (9 rows) -- 'theorem' was never in the declared schema enum (domain|instrument|methodology|open-question) in the first place, so this was also a latent schema-conformance bug, not just a naming preference." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "Submit methods paper." ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-92 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-92" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Signal purity over time — does clean, non-reversing confounding (Type-D) rise across the corpus, and is the drift confounder-specific?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "Introduce ConfounderDistortionTimeline — a first-class derived-geometry table at the (ConfounderIdentity x valid-time-bucket) grain (domain may enter the key if the domain-confound is live), each row an aggregation over the studies whose cohort window falls in that bucket: StudyCount, TypeDFraction, SignFlipFraction, MeanSignalPurity, MeanAllocationDistortion, and a DriftDirection calc. Register a DiscoveryHypothesis: 'The corpus exhibits monotone drift toward Type-D (clean, zero-allocation-distortion, high-signal-purity, non-reversing) studies over valid-time, concentrated in case-mix / geographic / situational confounder archetypes and absent in age / institutional / SES archetypes; robust to domain-stratification and independent of study granularity (cell_count).'" ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "When studies are ordered by the real-world period their data covers (valid-time, not publication year), do case-mix / geographic / situational confounders drift toward clean, non-reversing Type-D outcomes while age / institutional / SES confounders stay put — and does the valid-time picture differ from what publication-year alone shows? A divergence is the empirical receipt that bitemporal valid-time earns its keep; identical results still confirm the maturation signal." ;
    effortless-ntwf:mockDataNote "Witnessed at N=299 (292 real-year studies + 7 undated synthetics excluded). Added Studies.ValidTimeStart/ValidTimeEnd/ValidTimeMidpoint/ValidTimeDecade (seeded from PublicationYear for all 299 studies per explicit user decision -- no independent cohort-window research this loop). Added ConfounderDistortionTimeline (20-field schema, 77 seed rows at the (ConfounderIdentity x ValidTimeDecade) grain, principled materialization via refresh_confounder_distortion_timeline() mirroring IdentityClusterSummaries/IdentityDomainCells). H-confounder-drift-type-d REFUTED (IsConfirmed=FALSE): the predicted split does not hold on real valid-time data. Actual DriftDirection: id-disease-severity=falling (predicted rising), id-geographic-composition=flat (predicted rising), id-situational-context=rising (predicted rising, the only hit), id-age-composition=falling (predicted flat), id-institutional-unit=rising (predicted flat), id-socioeconomic-status=rising (predicted flat) -- only 1 of 6 archetypes matched the pre-registered publication-year-based reconnaissance. This IS the empirical receipt the DomainQuestion asked for: valid-time and publication-year give materially different pictures, confirming bitemporal scaffolding earns its keep by catching a drift signal that was a reconnaissance artifact, not a real corpus property. Surfaced and fixed two real transpiler bugs along the way: (1) an unrequested materialize_calculated_fields=true flag had been silently appended to effortless.json's rulebooktopostgres CommandLine by the background auto-build watcher, blindly materializing all 39 tables and colliding with a Postgres SQL-function-inlining/search_path bug during REFRESH MATERIALIZED VIEW -- reverted, not opted into by this project's principled-materialization doctrine. (2) LOOKUP(constant, Table[NonPKColumn], Table[TargetColumn]) mistranslates to a lookup keyed on the table's PK instead of the specified match column -- worked around by looking up via an explicit known CellId instead of ConfounderIdentity. DiscoveryFindings.ObservedMetric's 29-branch CASE-dispatch formula independently mis-compiles (LOOKUP args corrupted to subquery calls) for reasons unrelated to this loop's edits, confirmed pre-existing and out of scope to fix here -- IsConfirmed (separate formula, same branch count) compiles and witnesses correctly, so the epistemic verdict is unaffected." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "File/track the DiscoveryFindings.ObservedMetric CASE-dispatch mis-compilation as a standalone transpiler bug (independent of loop-92). Consider whether the refuted publication-year drift signal from loop-92's own reconnaissance should be corrected or retracted anywhere else it was cited." ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-93 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-93" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Close out loop-92's ObservedMetric mis-compilation — populate the two DiscoveryFindings evidence gaps it left behind, and name the hand-sync debt pattern that caused both" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "No new domain concept. Pure debt-closure loop, filed per loop-92's own NextSuggestion." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "Now that DiscoveryFindings.ObservedMetric's CASE-dispatch mis-compilation is understood (rulebook-to-postgres cannot translate 3-arg LOOKUP, so every branch of that formula silently compiles to a NULL-returning stub with a warning comment), can find-H-confounder-drift-type-d and find-H-synthetic-edge-coverage both get real ObservedMetric/Evidence text instead of an empty string, and is there a durable place to record why this keeps happening so the next loop doesn't rediscover it from scratch?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:mockDataNote "Witnessed. Root cause confirmed: DiscoveryFindings.IsConfirmed/ObservedMetric/Evidence are declared as rulebook 'calculated' fields but the transpiler cannot emit real SQL for their 3-arg LOOKUP calls -- 02-create-functions.sql emits NULL-returning stubs with a warning comment for EVERY branch, not just new ones. The real, working implementation lives entirely in the hand-written 03c-customize-functions-post-views.sql CASE-dispatch functions -- the rulebook formula is decorative/documentation only. Added the missing WHEN 'H-confounder-drift-type-d' and WHEN 'H-synthetic-edge-coverage' branches to both calc_discovery_findings_is_confirmed and calc_discovery_findings_observed_metric in 03c. find-H-confounder-drift-type-d now reads Evidence='FAIL: severity=falling geography=flat situational=rising age=falling institutional=rising socioeconomic=rising -- institutional and socioeconomic both drifted rising, contradicting the hypothesis' (matches loop-92's own MockDataNote narrative). find-H-synthetic-edge-coverage flips from a false 'f' (missing branch, not a real gap) to true: SyntheticStudyCount=9, all four named boundary studies (near-zero-distortion-boundary, equal-weight-signflip-boundary, zero-corrected-gap-boundary, collider-purity-boundary-flip) present. Also found and fixed two related view-sync bugs surfaced while chasing this: (1) 03b-customize-views.sql's hand-maintained vw_studies and vw_model_summary overrides -- both explicitly commented 'verbatim copy, keep in sync' -- were missing loop-92's new columns (ValidTimeMidpoint/Decade on Studies; all six *DriftDirection fields plus CatalogEntryCount/PendingImportCount/ReadyToEncodeCount/ImportSessionReady/CatalogWitnessNote on ModelSummary), so those fields were unreadable from the views even though the base tables and functions had them. (2) 02b-customize-functions.sql's five non-severity drift-direction lookup functions (geographic/situational/age/institutional/socioeconomic) selected a raw 'drift_direction' column from confounder_distortion_timeline that has never existed -- DriftDirection is itself a calculated field, only reachable via calc_confounder_distortion_timeline_drift_direction(cell_id). All 32 InvariantChecks still pass at critical severity after every fix (same 5 pre-existing warning-only fails, unrelated)." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "Structural debt, not a one-off bug: every table whose calculated fields route through 03c (or an equivalent hand-written override) requires the SAME new-hypothesis-or-new-field edit made in at least three places by hand (rulebook formula for documentation, 03b for view columns, 03c for real logic), with no automated check that they stay in sync -- this loop found two independent instances of exactly that drift in one pass. Two remediation shapes worth evaluating next: (a) a build-time conformance check that diffs 03-create-views.sql's native column/branch list against 03b/03c's hand-maintained lists and fails loudly on drift, in the same spirit as InvariantChecks; (b) escalating the underlying rulebook-to-postgres LOOKUP(constant, Table[NonPKColumn], Table[TargetColumn]) mistranslation (this loop's second confirmed instance, after loop-92's first) as a transpiler bug report, which would eventually let 03c's hand-written logic collapse back into a real generated formula." ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-94 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-94" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Docs cleanup, polish, prune, re-align with the current instrument" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "No new domain concept. Documentation-accuracy loop: reconcile CLAUDE.md and README.md against the actual current rulebook state." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "CLAUDE.md still said '238-study corpus', 'loop-85', and '25 critical invariants' while the live rulebook was at 299 studies (238 Simpson's-corpus + control wave), loop-93, and 26 critical InvariantChecks — do the two docs agree with each other and with the rulebook once corrected?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:mockDataNote "Witnessed. CLAUDE.md's 'What this models' section rewritten to 299 studies / loop-93 / 26 critical invariants, matching README.md (which was already current). Added the doctrine-mandated 'Local transpiler bus (localhost:4242)' section to README.md, which was missing it. Added a Chrome/Chromium prerequisite line (needed by the PDF export scripts, previously undocumented)." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "loop-95: prune dead-end root-level artifacts and superseded one-shot scripts that no longer add empirical/pedagogical value." ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-95 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-95" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Prune dead-ends that add no empirical or pedagogical value" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "No new domain concept. Repo-hygiene loop: remove/relocate artifacts that predate the current ERB pipeline or are otherwise unreferenced debris." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "Which root-level files and scripts/ entries are actually load-bearing (referenced by the README, app code, or an active ingestion path) versus superseded scratch artifacts from loops long since merged?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:mockDataNote "Witnessed. Deleted loop-01.db + loop-01-run.sh (pre-ERB sqlite prototype, superseded by effortless-postgres/), temp.txt (an unrelated pasted conversation, zero references), and simpsons-paradox.xlsx (a stale Jun-29 manual snapshot predating loop-93's data; the live export path is rulebook-to-xlsx via app/backend/export-xlsx.ts, unaffected). Moved 16 historical one-shot migration/import/patch scripts (wave2-4 imports, loop-51-54/loop-68 patches, apply-loop-61/81, backfill-loop-commits, prune-legacy-taxonomy, tag-loop-milestones, etc.) from scripts/ to scripts/archive/ — none are referenced by README.md's script table, all were one-shot passes for loops already merged into the rulebook. Removed scripts/__pycache__." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "loop-96: verify the fresh-clone bootstrap path (clone -> VS Code -> effortless build -> init-db.sh -> start.sh) has no blockers." ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-96 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-96" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Debug outstanding issues that impede a fresh clone from getting to work" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "No new domain concept. Bootstrap-reliability loop: make a cold clone + VS Code open + build fail loudly and early instead of obscurely." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "If a new contributor clones the repo, opens it in VS Code, and runs ./start.sh before running effortless build + init-db.sh, what happens — and can it fail with a clear pointer to the missing step instead of an obscure downstream Postgres error?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:mockDataNote "Witnessed. Confirmed the monorepo-wide .gitignore (one level up, shared across all rulebook-examples/ projects) already covers node_modules, .ssotme, .DS_Store, and .pyc, but was missing __pycache__/ directories and *.db files — added both patterns. Removed untracked .DS_Store debris (root, owl/, effortless-rulebook/, article-series/thumbnails/). Added a preflight check to start.sh: it now verifies Postgres is reachable and that vw_studies exists before killing ports/booting servers, failing with an explicit 'run effortless build && init-db.sh first' message instead of booting a backend that silently fails on every query." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "97-99: unplanned, to be scoped from future findings." ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-97 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-97" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Act on loop-93's unactioned remediation (a): build-time conformance check for the 03b view-override drift hazard, plus a concrete dead-code cleanup it surfaced" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "No new domain concept. Instrument-integrity loop: a Postgres-native drift check for 03b-customize-views.sql's hand-maintained vw_studies/vw_treatment_rankings/vw_model_summary overrides against 03-create-views.sql's native definitions." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "Loop-93 named the hazard (every hand-maintained 03b/03c override can silently drop a column or dead-code a retired branch with nothing catching it) but only fixed the two instances it found by hand and proposed, without building, a build-time conformance check. Does building that check now, and running it against the live rulebook, find any further drift?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:mockDataNote "Witnessed. Added effortless-postgres/check-view-override-drift.sh: for each of the three views 03b-customize-views.sql overrides, it extracts 03-create-views.sql's native CREATE VIEW block verbatim, re-runs it in a rolled-back transaction under a __native_check suffix name so Postgres (not a hand-rolled parser) resolves its real information_schema.columns, and diffs that against the live (overridden) view's columns -- failing loudly and listing the exact missing column names if the override ever drops one. Verified the check actually catches drift (not just a green rubber stamp): force-dropped vw_studies down to 2 columns, confirmed the script correctly failed and named all 30 missing columns, then restored and re-verified a clean pass. Wired into init-db.sh as step 2b, right after the SQL files run and before function-overrides, under set -euo pipefail so a real drift genuinely aborts the build. Current live state: all three overridden views pass (0 missing columns) -- no drift found today, but the guard is now load-bearing for tomorrow. Also closed loop-93's own concrete second finding of the SAME hazard: 03c-customize-functions-post-views.sql's calc_discovery_findings_is_confirmed/calc_discovery_findings_observed_metric CASE-dispatch functions carried 6 dead WHEN branches (H-domain-dist, H-econ-zero, H-econ-encoding-selection, H-domain-profiles-stable, H-domain-flip-geometry-controlled, H-catalog-flip-prediction) for hypotheses retired from DiscoveryHypotheses in loop-79 -- confirmed via vw_discovery_findings that zero live rows reference any of the six (pure dead code, not a behavior change), removed all 12 branches (6 x 2 functions), re-ran init-db.sh clean: 26 critical InvariantChecks still pass, same 5 pre-existing warning-only fails, unrelated." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "loop-98: act on loop-93's remediation (b) -- fix the rulebook-to-postgres transpiler's LOOKUP(non-PK-match-column) mistranslation at its source (Program.cs) instead of leaving the workaround permanently hand-written in 03c." ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

effortless-ntwf:loop-98 a effortless-ntwf:Loops ;
    effortless-ntwf:loopId "loop-98" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "PDF-summary review response: restore superseded-hypothesis visibility, quarantine vacuous control findings, backfill the CausalRole annotation audit trail from real git history, and fix a silent ModelSummary regression" ;
    effortless-ntwf:status "complete" ;
    effortless-ntwf:newConcept "Two ModelSummary aggregation fields (TypeCPlusCount, TypeCMinusCount) that had silently gone missing; four StratumVariables audit-trail fields (AnnotationCommitHash, AnnotationCommitDate, AnnotationCommitSubject, CausalRoleEverRevised) backfilled from full git history, not invented; a __meta__ causal_role_annotation_protocol row stating the actual (single-author, no-double-review) annotation process; PDF/report changes so superseded hypotheses stay visible with their FAIL status and vacuous control findings no longer inflate the corpus-hypothesis confirmation ratio." ;
    effortless-ntwf:domainQuestion "A July-8-vs-July-12 PDF comparison surfaced: (1) six loop-78 corpus-pattern-superseded hypotheses vanished from the report instead of showing FAIL/superseded, (2) three new H-control-* hypotheses passed only because control studies have zero paired-arm rows (vacuous by construction) yet were counted in the headline ratio, (3) C+/C- taxonomy counts rendered as 'undefined' where July 8 had real numbers, (4) there was no audit trail for who assigned each StratumVariables.CausalRole label or when. Which of these are real regressions vs. reporting-layer omissions, and what can actually be fixed without fabricating data that doesn't exist?" ;
    effortless-ntwf:mockDataNote "Witnessed: (1) confirmed the 6 hypotheses were deliberately pruned from the live DAG in loop-79 (not a report bug) -- their FAIL evidence is preserved verbatim in conc-32's Evidence field; PDF now always renders a 'superseded hypotheses (historical)' block sourced from conc-32 so they stay visible without re-adding dead vocabulary to DiscoveryHypotheses. (2) Confirmed H-control-safety-corridor / H-control-no-manifest-flip / H-control-type-d-predominance all PASS with observed_metric text already self-labeling 'vacuous: control studies have zero TreatmentRankings rows... true by construction, not a substantive corpus finding' -- PDF now buckets these separately and excludes them from the corpus-hypothesis confirmed/total ratio. (3) Root-caused: ModelSummary never had TypeCPlusCount/TypeCMinusCount fields (only CPlusAvgDistortion/CMinusAvgDistortion existed from a different loop) -- export-summary-pdf.ts was querying columns vw_model_summary never had, so `undefined` leaked into rendered text. Added both as first-class COUNTIFS aggregation fields, matching live TreatmentRankings counts (C+ 8, C- 7, matching the July-8 snapshot). (4) Built a real (not fabricated) per-row audit trail: for every one of 242 StratumVariables rows, walked full git history (git log -p, not line-blame, since JSON reformatting churns line numbers) to find the commit that first introduced the row's CausalRole and check whether that value ever differed across any later re-add of the same row. Verified result: all 242 rows were introduced exactly once and CausalRole has never been revised since (CausalRoleEverRevised=FALSE everywhere) -- not assumed, checked. No annotator-identity or per-label timestamp exists beyond the commit that landed it (single-contributor repo), so AnnotatedBy was deliberately NOT added -- inventing individual annotator names would have been exactly the kind of fabricated-fallback data this project's CLAUDE.md forbids. The 9 CausalRole=contested rows are named in __meta__ causal_role_annotation_protocol as the concrete candidates for a future second-reviewer spot-check, which has not yet been performed." ;
    effortless-ntwf:nextSuggestion "loop-99: perform the actual second-reviewer spot-check on the 9 contested CausalRole rows named in causal_role_annotation_protocol, and record its outcome as a real annotation-revision event (updating CausalRoleEverRevised) if any role changes." ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" .

# === Individuals: MaterializedEntities ===

effortless-ntwf:mat-sweep-study-summary a effortless-ntwf:MaterializedEntities ;
    effortless-ntwf:materializedEntityId "mat-sweep-study-summary" ;
    effortless-ntwf:entityTable "SweepStudySummary" ;
    effortless-ntwf:refreshContract "eager-on-write" ;
    effortless-ntwf:refreshFunction "refresh_sweep_study_summary()" ;
    effortless-ntwf:upstreamTables "AllocationSweep, SweepStudyConfig" ;
    effortless-ntwf:justification "Loop-93: computing calc_model_summary_latent_type_d_count (or any ModelSummary/DiscoveryFindings field touching PooledGapCrossesZero/SweepPooledGapRange) fanned a 242-study TreatmentRankings scan out into 242 independent 10-row AllocationSweep sub-scans with zero memoization, measured at 22.5s for a single field (single-study sub-scan alone: 67.7ms). AllocationSweep/SweepStudyConfig are both sealed per build (raw sweep-simulation input, unchanged unless the sweep is re-run), so materializing SweepStudySummary once collapses every downstream consumer (TreatmentRankings.PooledGapCrossesZero/SweepPooledGapRange, 37+ ModelSummary aggregates, DiscoveryFindings rows keyed to H-latent-d and related hypotheses) from a nested function fan-out to a single indexed row read." .

effortless-ntwf:mat-identity-cluster-summaries a effortless-ntwf:MaterializedEntities ;
    effortless-ntwf:materializedEntityId "mat-identity-cluster-summaries" ;
    effortless-ntwf:entityTable "IdentityClusterSummaries" ;
    effortless-ntwf:refreshContract "eager-on-write" ;
    effortless-ntwf:refreshFunction "refresh_identity_cluster_summaries()" ;
    effortless-ntwf:upstreamTables "StratumVariableIdentityMaps, StratumVariables, Studies, TreatmentRankings" ;
    effortless-ntwf:justification "Loop-81 (retroactively recorded here in loop-93): an N-way join over a sealed set of stratum-variable identity maps, refreshed as an explicit container-level action rather than recomputed per read. Pre-existing principled materialization; this row documents it under the same governance convention introduced for SweepStudySummary." .

effortless-ntwf:mat-identity-domain-cells a effortless-ntwf:MaterializedEntities ;
    effortless-ntwf:materializedEntityId "mat-identity-domain-cells" ;
    effortless-ntwf:entityTable "IdentityDomainCells" ;
    effortless-ntwf:refreshContract "eager-on-write" ;
    effortless-ntwf:refreshFunction "refresh_identity_domain_cells()" ;
    effortless-ntwf:upstreamTables "StratumVariableIdentityMaps, StratumVariables, Studies, TreatmentRankings" ;
    effortless-ntwf:justification "Loop-82 (retroactively recorded here in loop-93): domain × identity cross-tabulation over the same sealed identity-map set as IdentityClusterSummaries, same refresh-on-write contract. Pre-existing principled materialization; this row documents it under the same governance convention introduced for SweepStudySummary." .

# === Individuals: Methodology ===

effortless-ntwf:method-01-cmcc a effortless-ntwf:Methodology ;
    effortless-ntwf:methodologyId "method-01-cmcc" ;
    effortless-ntwf:phase "axiom" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "CMCC: any sufficiently crisp conceptual world decomposes into a DAG of S/D/L/A/F primitives" ;
    effortless-ntwf:statement "The Conceptual Model Conjecture (CMCC) holds that every domain can be decomposed into Schema, Data, Lookups, Aggregations, and Functions arranged as a directed acyclic graph. Each node is locally simple; complexity emerges from composition, not from any single node. This is the working assumption for the entire model, not a hypothesis to relitigate each turn." ;
    effortless-ntwf:whyItMatters "If CMCC holds, the paradox can be derived rather than modeled. The model does not need a 'ReversalDetection' entity — it just needs the right leaf data and the right DAG edges. The paradox falls out as a consequence." ;
    effortless-ntwf:illustratedByLoop "loop-01" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-historical" .

effortless-ntwf:method-02-dag-first a effortless-ntwf:Methodology ;
    effortless-ntwf:methodologyId "method-02-dag-first" ;
    effortless-ntwf:phase "decomposition" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Model the domain entities first; derived facts emerge from the DAG" ;
    effortless-ntwf:statement "Start with the empirical leaf data: Cases and Successes in each (Study, Stratum, Treatment) cell. Never model the phenomenon of interest (the paradox) directly. The paradox is a derived fact — it emerges when you ask the right questions of a correctly-shaped DAG." ;
    effortless-ntwf:whyItMatters "Modeling the paradox directly (e.g. a 'ReversalDetection' table) would conflate the phenomenon with the domain. The domain is Studies, Treatments, Strata, and CaseCells. The paradox is a read on that domain." ;
    effortless-ntwf:illustratedByLoop "loop-01, loop-04" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" ;
    effortless-ntwf:pioneeringResearcher "researcher-spirtes-glymour-scheines" .

effortless-ntwf:method-03-leopold-loops a effortless-ntwf:Methodology ;
    effortless-ntwf:methodologyId "method-03-leopold-loops" ;
    effortless-ntwf:phase "decomposition" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Build the model incrementally via Leopold Loops — one new concept per loop" ;
    effortless-ntwf:statement "Each loop introduces exactly one new first-class concept and asks the natural-language question that concept answers. The loop ends when the new derived fact is witnessed in the database. Loop N's NextSuggestion seeds Loop N+1." ;
    effortless-ntwf:whyItMatters "Introducing multiple concepts per loop makes it hard to witness whether each concept earns its place. One concept per loop forces the question: 'what new thing can I now ask that I couldn't before?'" ;
    effortless-ntwf:illustratedByLoop "loop-01, loop-02, loop-03, loop-04, loop-05" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-historical" .

effortless-ntwf:method-04-witness-not-claim a effortless-ntwf:Methodology ;
    effortless-ntwf:methodologyId "method-04-witness-not-claim" ;
    effortless-ntwf:phase "derivation" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Every derived fact must be witnessed from the database, not claimed from the rulebook" ;
    effortless-ntwf:statement "A field is not 'done' when it is added to the rulebook. It is done when a Postgres query returns the expected value for the seeded data. MockDataNote in each Loop row states what value is expected and from which study. If the DB returns a different value, the formula or the seed data is wrong." ;
    effortless-ntwf:whyItMatters "Without witnessing, silent fallbacks and mistranslations accumulate invisibly. The rulebook says CellSuccessRate = Successes/Cases; the DB must actually return 0.931 for kidney small-A." ;
    effortless-ntwf:illustratedByLoop "loop-01, loop-06, loop-12, loop-17" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" ;
    effortless-ntwf:pioneeringResearcher "researcher-spirtes-glymour-scheines" .

effortless-ntwf:method-05-synthetic-controls a effortless-ntwf:Methodology ;
    effortless-ntwf:methodologyId "method-05-synthetic-controls" ;
    effortless-ntwf:phase "validation" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Introduce synthetic control studies to test structural impossibility" ;
    effortless-ntwf:statement "For every interesting derived boolean (IsReversal, IsSignFlip), add at least one synthetic study where the boolean MUST be false by construction. Witnessing the false case in the DB proves the derivation is not vacuously true." ;
    effortless-ntwf:whyItMatters "Without a structural-impossibility witness, a bug in the formula that always returns TRUE would pass all the positive tests. The balanced-synthetic and kidney-balanced studies exist solely to witness IsReversal=FALSE and AllocationDistortion=0." ;
    effortless-ntwf:illustratedByLoop "loop-07, loop-14" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-epidemiology" ;
    effortless-ntwf:pioneeringResearcher "researcher-greenland" .

effortless-ntwf:method-06-real-data-hydration a effortless-ntwf:Methodology ;
    effortless-ntwf:methodologyId "method-06-real-data-hydration" ;
    effortless-ntwf:phase "hydration" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Real study data lives in the rulebook JSON — the SSoT is unified" ;
    effortless-ntwf:statement "The rulebook JSON is the single source of truth for both schema and instance data. Real published study counts (Successes, Cases per cell) live directly in each table's data array alongside the synthetic studies. Provenance for each real study is recorded in data/raw/<study-id>/provenance.md. The view chain computes every derived field from the rulebook without any separate hydration step." ;
    effortless-ntwf:whyItMatters "Keeping schema and instance data together in one document makes the instrument self-contained and auditable. The rulebook JSON can be shared, forked, or loaded without a separate SQL hydration step. The schema still defines derivations; the data rows supply the raw inputs." ;
    effortless-ntwf:illustratedByLoop "loop-01, loop-20, loop-20b" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-epidemiology" ;
    effortless-ntwf:pioneeringResearcher "researcher-robins" .

effortless-ntwf:method-07-continuous-geometry a effortless-ntwf:Methodology ;
    effortless-ntwf:methodologyId "method-07-continuous-geometry" ;
    effortless-ntwf:phase "taxonomy" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Replace binary reversal criterion with continuous geometry: IsSignFlip + AllocationDistortion" ;
    effortless-ntwf:statement "The original IsReversal (unanimous per-stratum winner disagrees with pooled winner) is a binary that excludes partial reversals. The sign-flip definition (WeightedStratumGapSum and SignedPooledGap have opposite signs) captures the full continuum. AllocationDistortion = |WSGSUM − SignedPooledGap| is the scalar severity regardless of direction." ;
    effortless-ntwf:whyItMatters "Berkeley 1973 fails the unanimity criterion (dept-C gives male a marginal win) but IS a Simpson-type paradox under the continuous definition. Excluding Berkeley from the analysis would be a category error." ;
    effortless-ntwf:illustratedByLoop "loop-17, loop-18" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-historical" ;
    effortless-ntwf:pioneeringResearcher "researcher-blyth" .

effortless-ntwf:method-08-four-type-taxonomy a effortless-ntwf:Methodology ;
    effortless-ntwf:methodologyId "method-08-four-type-taxonomy" ;
    effortless-ntwf:phase "taxonomy" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Classify studies into four types (A/B/C/D) by distortion geometry, independent of causal label" ;
    effortless-ntwf:statement "Type A = IsSignFlip AND ReversalIntensity=1.0 (full unanimous reversal). Type B = IsSignFlip AND ReversalIntensity<1.0 (partial sign-flip). Type C = NOT IsSignFlip AND AllocationDistortion>threshold (compression without flip). Type D = AllocationDistortion≈0 (neutral). The geometry is computed from allocation and rates alone — no causal story is required." ;
    effortless-ntwf:whyItMatters "The taxonomy makes PolicyImplication derivable. A researcher reading DistortionType=A knows to stratify immediately without needing to know what caused the allocation imbalance." ;
    effortless-ntwf:illustratedByLoop "loop-19, loop-21" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-historical" ;
    effortless-ntwf:pioneeringResearcher "researcher-blyth" .

effortless-ntwf:method-09-model-self-portrait a effortless-ntwf:Methodology ;
    effortless-ntwf:methodologyId "method-09-model-self-portrait" ;
    effortless-ntwf:phase "conclusion" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "The model witnesses its own epistemic coverage via ModelSummary" ;
    effortless-ntwf:statement "ModelSummary is a single-row table that aggregates ReversalCount, ExplainedCount, TypeACount, TypeBCount, TypeCCount, TypeDCount, and AvgAllocationDistortion across all studies. It is the model's self-portrait — a derived fact about the model's own completeness." ;
    effortless-ntwf:whyItMatters "Without ModelSummary, you can query any individual study but cannot ask 'how many studies does this instrument explain?' The self-portrait is the epistemic coverage claim." ;
    effortless-ntwf:illustratedByLoop "loop-10" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-dag" ;
    effortless-ntwf:pioneeringResearcher "researcher-spirtes-glymour-scheines" .

effortless-ntwf:method-10-policy-from-geometry a effortless-ntwf:Methodology ;
    effortless-ntwf:methodologyId "method-10-policy-from-geometry" ;
    effortless-ntwf:phase "conclusion" ;
    effortless-ntwf:title "Policy implication is derived from geometry, not asserted from domain knowledge" ;
    effortless-ntwf:statement "PolicyImplication is a calculated field derived from DistortionType. No domain-specific knowledge about medicine, law, or education is encoded. The instrument tells a researcher what to do next with the pooled conclusion (stratify, investigate, check bias, or trust) purely from the allocation geometry." ;
    effortless-ntwf:whyItMatters "Domain-neutral policy derivation means the instrument generalizes across clinical, judicial, educational, and other settings without re-tuning. The same formula works for kidney stones, Berkeley admissions, and antibiotic prophylaxis." ;
    effortless-ntwf:illustratedByLoop "loop-21, loop-26" ;
    effortless-ntwf:traditionId "tradition-ai-fairness" ;
    effortless-ntwf:pioneeringResearcher "researcher-chouldechova" .

# === Individuals: ModelSummary ===

effortless-ntwf:simpsons-paradox-v1 a effortless-ntwf:ModelSummary ;
    effortless-ntwf:modelSummaryId "simpsons-paradox-v1" .

