    effortless-ntwf:keyContribution "Proved the fairness impossibility theorem (2017): when recidivism prevalence differs across groups, satisfying calibration necessarily produces disparate error rates — base-rate divergence (the paradox mechanism) makes irreconcilable fairness criteria structurally unavoidable." ;
